Since previously non-marathon runners such as Gebrselassie and Kenyan Paul Tergat have turned to longer distances, the marathon record has fallen by more than two minutes in the last decade since Brazil's Ronaldo da Costa won in 1998 in Berlin with a score of 2:06:05.
