Recent research has shown that religious belief acts as a kind of pain reliever that may have already facilitated the deaths of Catholic martyrs.
Scientists at the University of Oxford conducted an interesting experiment to explore how belief in God affects people’s perceptions of pain, according to the British Telegraph.
In a rather bizarre investigation, 12 Catholics and an equal number of atheists were electro-shocked while all of them studied a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
