The current European safety standard sets the maximum noise level to be emitted by portable music players at 100 dB, but there is growing concern about hearing loss caused by overuse of such sound sources.
At the same time, there are solutions, such as reducing the level and duration of noise damage, which can significantly reduce these hearing impairments.
In its opinion, the EU Scientific Committee explains that users of portable players who listen to music at a high volume (more than 89 decibels) for five hours a week exceed the current maximum level of noise exposure to workplace noise.
If you listen to music for a long time under similar conditions, there is a risk of permanent hearing loss after five years.
This affects approximately 5 to 10 percent of people using portable devices, which could amount to 2.5 to 10 million people in the EU.
